text: Sonny Seidel-Jung (born 7 May 1968) is a German former taekwondo practitioner. She competed at the 1988 Summer Olympics, where taekwondo was a demonstration sport, in the welterweight class, finishing third. She represented West Germany in the 1992 Summer Olympics, in the lightweight class. At the 1988 European Taekwondo Championships, she won the silver medal for West Germany. In 1992, she became European Champion for Germany in the -65kg category. She was seven times German champion. She was a member of Chung-Gun Hammersbach in Hammersbach. == References == Category:1968 births Category:Living people Category:Olympians for Germany Category:Taekwondo practitioners
